The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 13 September is 71,549 (8,246.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 08 September, there were 2,155 new confirmed cases (248.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 01 September, there were 2,227 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 3% (72 fewer cases).
